      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>985</offset>
        <text>The bacterial community in the desiccating sediment changed significantly from the controls after 14 days of desiccation (salinity 144).
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>1122</offset>
        <text>Rewetting did not cause a return to the original community composition, but led to a further change.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">9</infon>
        <offset>1223</offset>
        <text>Pyrosequencing analysis of 16S rRNA genes amplified from the sediment revealed diverse microbial responses, for example desiccation enabled haloversatile Marinobacter species to increase their relative abundance, and thus take advantage of rewetting to grow rapidly and dominate the community.
</text>
        <annotation id="T10">
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <infon key="brat-id">T10</infon>
          <location length="8" offset="1401"/>
          <text>increase</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T11">
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <infon key="brat-id">T11</infon>
          <location length="24" offset="1410"/>
          <text>their relative abundance</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E6">
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <infon key="brat-id">E6</infon>
          <node refid="T10" role="Increase"/>
          <node refid="T11" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">10</infon>
        <offset>1517</offset>
        <text>A temporal sequence of effects of desiccation and rewetting were thus observed, but the most notable feature was the overall resistance and resilience of the microbial community.
</text>
      </sentence>
